Formaldehyde is a key chemical that finds applications across various industries due to its versatile properties. One major segment in the formaldehyde market is based on the type of formaldehyde products, with distinctions between paraformaldehyde, formalin, and urea formaldehyde. Paraformaldehyde is widely used in applications like adhesives and resins, while formalin is commonly employed in healthcare for disinfection purposes. On the other hand, urea formaldehyde is predominantly utilized in wood panels and particle boards due to its adhesive properties. Another crucial segment is based on the applications of formaldehyde, encompassing resins, textiles, paper, wood panels, and various other sectors. The end-user segment includes construction, healthcare, automotive, furniture manufacturing, and others, showcasing the widespread utilization of formaldehyde in different industries.

